%N A337818 Odd integers k>=3 such that k*(k-1)/2 divides 2^((k-1)/2)+1.
%C A337818 Computed terms are prime. Is it always the case? If not it would be interesting to compute the pseudoprimes.
%C A337818 Conjecture: a(n) == 1 mod 162 for n >= 6. The next few larger terms of the form 162*k+1 are: 44165935747, 46696027123, 85683674179, 88567070707, 101297654083, 131264938963, 131315541283, 177876176419, 195689448883, 196838306227, 213339588643, 310256425603, 378897238243, 502106519683, 588454831747, 611537689459, 641551809187, 735075731107, 745956214867, 755236606483, 771153067603, 872146803043 (and they are all primes). - _Chai Wah Wu_, Oct 06 2020
%C A337818 The conjecture fails, as a(30) = 48269073907 (prime). - _Bill McEachen_, Jul 11 2025
